Sentencas: The degradation of GDC interlayer is one of the key issues in the long-term stability of LSCF cathode-YSZ electrolyte based solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces

Sentencas: Here we demonstrate that the cathode microstructure has a strong influence on the stability of GDC interlayer and cation diffusion behavior of LSCF/GDC/YSZ triplets.
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces

Sentencas: LSCF was prepared into two distinct morphologies: porous layers by screen-printing and dense layers by pulsed laser deposition (PLD).
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces

Sentencas: Dense GDC barriers by PLD were applied to both porous and dense LSCF cathodes.
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces

Sentencas: Interdiffusion and microstructural evolution were investigated at temperatures of 800 degrees C to 1000 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, both cathodes showed no apparent formation of SrZrO3 at the GDC/YSZ interface.
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces

Sentencas: Instead, SrZrO3 formed at the LSCF/GDC interface, and was more evident for the porous LSCF annealed at 900 degrees C.
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces

Sentencas: At 1000 degrees C, severe cation interdiffusion at the LSCF/GDC interface became remarkable for the porous cathode, which exhibited rapid degradation of the GDC layer accompanied by the severe SrZrO3 formation; by contrast the dense cathode only showed localized SrZrO3 grains.
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces

Sentencas: The superior barrier stability of GDC in a dense cathode can be related to the air-tight interface which would minimize microstructural degradation occurring near the oxygen/LSCF/GDC triple phase boundary.
Titulo: Influence of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Microstructure on GDC Interlayer Stability and Cation Diffusion across the LSCF/GDC/YSZ Interfaces
